race.comment: WACO KID (6) has found form and looks set to go on with it. He broke the maiden effortlessly two back at Wangaratta and went on with it at Cranbourne with another smart victory. This looks a fairly winnable race and he should be hard to hold out once more. EXPRESS GUARD (2) is finding it tough to win but continues to race well. He was beaten under a length last time out and should be right there again. ITSUKUSHIMA (3) has just found one better his past three outings but keeps racing well. He'll likely go straight to the front here and that will be beneficial on this track. BLUSHING TYCOON (1) did enough fresh at Cranbourne in a bunched finish and will be fitter. He doesn't win out of turn but is good enough on his day. MISLIGHT (10) broke her maiden well last time and could measure up.
